I think I found the problem. I was able to constantly reproduce this issue by shutting down the active CLC while bringing up the standby. The shutdown request was given at the moment the Partition cache was being built. Basically, since the DB is going down, the CacheLoader.load() method is calling on Databases.awaitSynchronized() which will spin for about 2 minutes prior calling itself again for each partition. 

{noformat}
2013-11-07 12:30:30 ERROR 000000046 Topology                 | CHECK:null  arn:euca:eucalyptus:PARTI00:cluster:CC_102/ ENABLED->ENABLED=NOTREADY [Cluster response includes _return=false:DescribeResourcesResponseType:null:return=false:epoch=null:status=ERROR]
2013-11-07 12:32:57 ERROR 000000015 Component                | com.eucalyptus.bootstrap.Databases$DatabaseStateException: Transaction begin failed due to concurrent database synchronization: [Host 10.111.1.69 #312 /10.111.1.69 coordinator=pending booting db:outofdate started=1383856084120 [/10.111.1.69]] for caller:
2013-11-07 12:32:57 ERROR 000000015 ServiceTransitions       | com.eucalyptus.util.fsm.TransitionException: WalrusBootstrapper.enable( ): failed because of: Transaction begin failed due to concurrent database synchronization: [Host 10.111.1.69 #312 /10.111.1.69 coordinator=pending booting db:outofdate started=1383856084120 [/10.111.1.69]] for caller:
2013-11-07 12:34:57 ERROR 000001453 Component                | com.eucalyptus.bootstrap.Databases$DatabaseStateException: Transaction begin failed due to concurrent database synchronization: [Host 10.111.1.69 #312 /10.111.1.69 coordinator=pending booting db:outofdate started=1383856084120 [/10.111.1.69]] for caller:
2013-11-07 12:34:57 ERROR 000000856 TCPListener              | java.net.SocketException: Socket closed
{noformat}

Essentially, the processes will terminate but this could take a very long time depending on how many partition you have (2 minutes x 2 per partitions). I added some code that checks wether or not the system is being shutdown within the 2 minute loop so we can exit early and throw an exception in order to prevent calling itself more than once. Perhaps the DatabaseStateException exception would be more appropriate call path (but there's still recursion in the load() method)? See the code below including my change:

{code}
public class Partitions {
  private static final LoadingCache<String, Partition> partitionMap = CacheBuilder.newBuilder().build(
    new CacheLoader<String, Partition>() {
      @Override
      public Partition load( final String input ) {
        try {
          Databases.awaitSynchronized( );
          EntityTransaction db = Entities.get( Partition.class );
          Partition p = null;
          try {
            p = Entities.uniqueResult( Partition.newInstanceNamed( input ) );
            db.commit( );
            return p;
          } catch ( NoSuchElementException ex ) {
            db.rollback( );
            throw ex;
          } catch ( Exception ex ) {
            db.rollback( );
            throw Exceptions.toUndeclared( ex );
          }
        } catch ( NoSuchElementException ex ) {
          throw ex;
        } catch ( DatabaseStateException ex ) {
          Databases.awaitSynchronized( );
          return load( input ); <======== Recursion if DatabaseStateException is used
        } catch ( RuntimeException ex ) {
          throw ex; <======= Early termination if RuntimeException is used
        }
      }
    });
  }
}

public class Databases {
  public static void awaitSynchronized( ) {
    if ( !isVolatile( ) ) {
      return;
    } else {
      Collection<StackTraceElement> stack = Threads.filteredStack( stackFilter );
      String caller = ( stack.isEmpty( )
        ? ""
        : stack.iterator( ).next( ).toString( ) );
      for ( int i = 0; i < MAX_TX_START_SYNC_RETRIES && isVolatile( ); i++ ) {
        if (Bootstrap.isShuttingDown()) <============== My added check
            throw new RuntimeException( "Transaction being failed due to system being shutdown: " + caller );
        try {
          TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS.sleep( 1000 );
          LOG.debug( "Transaction blocked on sync: " + caller );
        } catch ( InterruptedException ex ) {
          Exceptions.maybeInterrupted( ex );
          return;
        }
      }
      if ( isVolatile( ) ) {
        throw new DatabaseStateException( "Transaction begin failed due to concurrent database synchronization: " + Hosts.listDatabases( )
                                          + " for caller:\n"
                                          + Joiner.on( "\n\tat " ).join( stack ) );
      }
    }
  }
}
{code}

I'm running a QA HA sequence overnight with these changes. You can see it using git show --color 7d003a094602f1d8f1854c9206b4c3fa2eda021f.
